                    "text": "The scheme “Quality Paddy Seed Distribution”, introduced on 22nd August 2011 by the Agriculture-Farmers Welfare Department, Tamil Nadu, offers a subsidy of ₹5/- per kg on certified paddy seeds. Farmers can avail this benefit when purchasing seeds from Agricultural Extension Centers. This initiative helps reduce the cost burden on farmers, encouraging them to use high-quality paddy seeds for improved crop yields."
